goto http://www.docker.com/

download docker for MacOS

also download VS code

open terminal and do the following :

- git clone https://github.com/inpyjama/c-ninja-listings.git
- cd c-ninja-listings
- bash setup.sh [the guest is a Docker container that's being created and managed by Docker commands within the script]
- bash 
- c-ninja [enter docker environment]
- cd test
- make

open VS code an terminal :
- code --install-extension ms-vscode-remote.remote-containers
- code --install-extension ms-vscode-remote.remote-ssh
- code --install-extension ms-vscode-remote.remote-ssh-edit
- code --install-extension ms-vscode.remote-explorer
- code --install-extension zhwu95.riscv
- code --install-extension ZixuanWang.linkerscript

after this we will have docker container having the similar folder structure as c-ninja-listings (because of setup.sh)
